                  </hi>. I am a clerk to Glyn, Mills, and Co., 67, Lombard Street—we had no customer named Walter Hutchinson on 15th October—these forms are out of a very old customer's cheque-book; I cannot tell whose now.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18781118-name-113" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18781118-name-113" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18781118-name-113" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18781118-name-113" type="given" value="JOHN RICHARD"></interp>JOHN RICHARD BROWN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am manager of the Hermitage Bonded Vaults, East Smithfield—this (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is one of our warrants for three hogsheads of brandy, arid this is the delivery order upon which the warrant was issued and lodged at our place. (<hi rend="italic">This was signed</hi> "<hi rend="italic">Thomas Ming and Co.</hi>")—I received these four orders; three are for sampling these three hogsheads of brandy, and one is to prepare the warrant.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
